.TH REDSTR 1 "November 2025" "redstr 0.2.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
redstr \- Red team string transformation tool for offensive security operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B redstr
[\fIMODE\fR] \fITEXT\fR
.br
.B redstr
\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBredstr\fR is a comprehensive string obfuscation and transformation tool for
red team operations, penetration testing, and security research. It provides
30+ transformation functions for WAF bypass, XSS evasion, SQL injection testing,
phishing domain generation, and bot detection evasion.
.PP
The tool is designed for security professionals building tools like Caido,
Burp Suite extensions, phishing frameworks (EvilJinx), and bot detection evasion
systems.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.SH MODES
.SS "Basic Transformations"
.TP
.B random, r
Random capitalization (default mode)
.TP
.B alternate, a
Alternate upper/lower case
.TP
.B inverse, i
Invert the case of each letter
.TP
.B reverse, rv
Reverse the string
.SS "Case Conversion"
.TP
.B camel, c
Convert to camelCase
.TP
.B snake, s
Convert to snake_case
.TP
.B kebab, k
Convert to kebab-case
.SS "Security Testing - Obfuscation"
.TP
.B leetspeak, l
Convert to leetspeak for filter evasion
.TP
.B homoglyph, h
Substitute with lookalike characters for phishing
.TP
.B unicode, u
Random unicode variations for normalization testing
.TP
.B zalgo, z
Add zalgo combining characters for display testing
.TP
.B rot13
Apply ROT13 cipher transformation
.TP
.B vowel-swap, vs
Swap vowels randomly for pattern matching tests
.TP
.B double, d
Double random characters for validation testing
.TP
.B space-variants, sv
Use various Unicode space characters
.TP
.B mixed-encoding, me
Mix character encodings (HTML entities + Unicode)
.SS "Encoding and Obfuscation"
.TP
.B base64, b64
Encode to Base64 for payload obfuscation
.TP
.B url-encode, url
URL/percent encoding for web security testing
.TP
.B hex-encode, hex
Encode to hexadecimal
.TP
.B hex-mixed, hm
Mixed hex formats (\\x, %, 0x, &#x) for detection evasion
.SS "Injection Testing"
.TP
.B sql-comment, sql
Insert SQL comment patterns for injection testing
.TP
.B xss-tags, xss
Generate XSS tag variations for filter evasion
.TP
.B case-swap, cs
Random case swapping for WAF bypass
.TP
.B null-byte, nb
Insert null byte representations for null byte attacks
.TP
.B path-traversal, pt
Generate path traversal patterns (../ variations)
.TP
.B command-injection, ci
Insert command injection separators (; | && ||)
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Basic random capitalization:
.RS
redstr "Hello World"
.br
Output: HeLlO wOrLd
.RE
.PP
Leetspeak for filter bypass:
.RS
redstr leetspeak "password123"
.br
Output: p@55w0rd123
.RE
.PP
Homoglyph substitution for phishing:
.RS
redstr homoglyph "admin@example.com"
.br
Output: аdmіn@еxаmple.com
.RE
.PP
SQL injection testing:
.RS
redstr sql-comment "SELECT * FROM users"
.br
Output: SELECT --* FROM users
.RE
.PP
XSS payload obfuscation:
.RS
redstr xss-tags "<script>alert(1)</script>"
.br
Output: Encoded variations
.RE
.PP
Base64 encoding:
.RS
redstr base64 "secret payload"
.br
Output: c2VjcmV0IHBheWxvYWQ=
.RE
.PP
Path traversal testing:
.RS
redstr path-traversal "/etc/passwd"
.br
Output: ../etc/../passwd
.RE
